    <briefdescription>
<para>Memory ordering primitives for cross-core and ISR safety. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Provides acquire/release semantics for lock-free data structures that are shared between CPU cores (AMP multicore) or between ISR and main context.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Compile-time cost model</title><para></para>
</simplesect>
When <computeroutput>SYN_USE_MULTICORE</computeroutput> is <bold>off</bold> (the default), the acquire/release functions compile to plain volatile reads and writes — identical to what the code would do without barriers. Zero overhead.</para>
<para>When <computeroutput>SYN_USE_MULTICORE</computeroutput> is <bold>on</bold>, the functions insert hardware memory barriers (via <computeroutput>syn_port_memory_barrier()</computeroutput>) at the correct points to ensure cross-core visibility.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Memory ordering model</title><para></para>
</simplesect>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>STORE_RELEASE:</bold> All prior writes are visible before this store. Use after writing data, before publishing the index.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>LOAD_ACQUIRE:</bold> No subsequent reads can be reordered before this load. Use after reading an index, before accessing the data it guards.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Example: SPSC ring buffer with correct ordering</title><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>Producer<sp/>(core<sp/>0):</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">buf[head]<sp/>=<sp/>data;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__barrier_8h_1a46c96e264c231fce46e1bafba6f0475a" kindref="member">SYN_STORE_RELEASE</ref>(&amp;rb-&gt;head,<sp/>next_head);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>Consumer<sp/>(core<sp/>1):</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">size_t</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>h<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="syn__barrier_8h_1a3910188c1e4ab3953dd7a9c2ff88e9e6" kindref="member">SYN_LOAD_ACQUIRE</ref>(&amp;rb-&gt;head);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordflow">if</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>(h<sp/>!=<sp/>tail)<sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>x<sp/>=<sp/>buf[tail];<sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>guaranteed<sp/>to<sp/>see<sp/>data<sp/>written<sp/>before<sp/>head</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">}</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
